Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'DWI' from weighting dropdown menu on Page 03
And I go to Page 06 of Head MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Diffuse' from 'Finding' dropdown menu
And I select 'I describe' or 'I know' radio button

When I select 'Characterization I' tab
Then 'Circumscribed' radio button is enabled
And 'Non-circumscribed' radio button is enabled

And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

And 'Round' radio button is enabled
And 'Oval' radio button is enabled
And 'Patchy' radio button is enabled
And 'Areal' radio button is enabled

And 'T1w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'T2w signal' slider bar is enabled
And 'FLAIR signal' slider bar is enabled

And 'Signal void' checkbox is enabled
And 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is enabled

And 'Cysts' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Signal voids' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hemorrhage' checkbox is enabled

And 'Confluent' checkbox is enabled
And 'Mass effect' checkbox is enabled
And 'Infiltration' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Signal void' checkbox
Then 'Calcification' radio button is enabled
And 'Blood' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Hemorrhage' checkbox
Then 'Micro bleeding' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hemorrhagic lacunae' checkbox is enabled

When I set 'T1w signal' slider to position 'Hypeintens'
Then it is stays on this position

When I set 'T2w signal' slider to position 'Hypeintens'
Then it is stays on this position

When I set 'FLAIR signal' slider to position 'Hypeintens'
Then it is stays on this position
